i enjoy this song so much, partly because of the meaningful lyrics.  
- i think "I do what I want with who I like", "Everybody tells me to play nice", "Sometimes I like to go play dirty/Just like all of the ** boys do", "Iâ€™ll just do it like the boys say/Iâ€™m gettinâ€™ mine, gettinâ€™ mine", and "But my body donâ€™t belong to nah-uh-uh none of them though" are lines that debunk toxic views about women. women have always been told to act all nice and innocent to attract men, or behave "loyally" to men. but the truth is that women should be allowed to engage in and break out of any relationships as they wish because they know what's best for them, not men. as blackpink says, "Thatâ€™s my choice and thereâ€™s no one Iâ€™m hurting", so why don't we let women have free will without criticizing them all the time for wanting to have worthwhile relationships?
- and of course, "no oneâ€™s keeping tally", nobody really cares what you're doing. blackpink convinces us to be ourselves and refrain from agonizing ourselves with people's judgements, and i think that's a mindset that everybody needs to own.
